00:55:33.850 --> 00:55:40.110
The problem is, as I say, is
the Earth like a water balloon

00:55:40.110 --> 00:55:40.980
or like an ocean?

00:55:40.980 --> 00:55:44.620
Tesla thought that the Earth
was like a water balloon, which

00:55:44.620 --> 00:55:47.520
it was filled with an
incompressible fluid.

00:55:47.520 --> 00:55:51.160
And if you pumped, like he
shows on the left-hand side,

00:55:51.160 --> 00:55:56.360
at a certain frequency, i.e. the
resonant frequency of the Earth

00:55:56.360 --> 00:55:59.000
or the water
balloon, eventually,

00:55:59.000 --> 00:56:02.400
you'd reach the point where
with each subsequent stroke

00:56:02.400 --> 00:56:06.850
of the little pump, you'd
have water popping out

00:56:06.850 --> 00:56:08.330
of these one-way valves.

00:56:08.330 --> 00:56:10.816
Now, we're using a
hydraulic analogy here.

00:56:10.816 --> 00:56:12.690
Tesla, of course, is
talking about doing this

00:56:12.690 --> 00:56:14.410
with electrical energy.

00:56:14.410 --> 00:56:20.790
The problem is, how
does the Earth respond

00:56:20.790 --> 00:56:23.100
to that electrical energy?

00:56:23.100 --> 00:56:25.200
Is the Earth like an
incompressible fluid,

00:56:25.200 --> 00:56:26.960
or is it like a
compressible fluid?

00:56:26.960 --> 00:56:30.580
In other words, is
the situation such

00:56:30.580 --> 00:56:33.170
that if you threw a
rock into the ocean,

00:56:33.170 --> 00:56:34.880
the waves don't
travel from where

00:56:34.880 --> 00:56:37.850
I grew up in New Jersey
all the way to Spain?

00:56:37.850 --> 00:56:42.510
Eventually, through
friction in the fluid, i.e.

00:56:42.510 --> 00:56:44.910
the ocean, the waves peter out.

00:56:44.910 --> 00:56:48.360
And that's how the
Earth actually responds

00:56:48.360 --> 00:56:50.940
to electromagnetic waves.

00:56:50.940 --> 00:56:52.810
OK, so that's my understanding.

